  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, potential legal consequences can include:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Federal money laundering charges\n- Potential felony conviction\n- Significant prison time (typically 10-20 years)\n- Large monetary fines\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Seizure of assets related to laundering\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Potential civil forfeiture of property\n\n3. Additional potential consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n- Immigration complications\n\n4. Prosecution details\n- Investigation by agencies like FBI, IRS\n- Evidence gathering\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n\n5. Sentencing factors\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Prior criminal history\n- Specific circumstances of the crime\n\nThe exact consequences depend on specific circumstances, jurisdiction, and case details.",
